{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"70757c65-7a80-4dae-a49e-7238c9232123","content":"In your `App.xaml.cs`, override `CreateWindow` and subscribe to the lifecycle events on the returned `Window`:\n\n```csharp\nprotected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)\n{\n    var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);\n\n    window.Created += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Created\");\n    window.Activated += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Activated\");\n    window.Deactivated += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Deactivated\");\n    window.Stopped += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Stopped\");\n    window.Resumed += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Resumed\");\n    window.Destroying += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Destroying\");\n    window.Backgrounding += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Backgrounding\");\n\n    return window;\n}\n```\n\n**Event flow:**\n\n| Transition | Events fired |\n|---|---|\n| App launch | Created → Activated |\n| Sent to background | Deactivated → Stopped (+ Backgrounding on iOS/Mac) |\n| Returned to foreground | Resumed → Activated |\n| App closed | Destroying |\n\n> **Note:** `Backgrounding` only fires on iOS and Mac Catalyst. Use it to save state via `BackgroundingEventArgs.State`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"00d53f6d-24f4-477b-aa67-d12c89f6e105","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about subscribing to Window lifecycle events in a .NET MAUI app for debugging/logging purposes. This is a general knowledge question about .NET MAUI that I can answer directly without needing to search the codebase.\n\nIn .NET MAUI, the `Window` class exposes several lifecycle events that correspond to the app's state transitions. Let me provide a concise, helpful answer.\n\nThe Window lifecycle events in .NET MAUI are:\n- Created\n- Activated\n- Deactivated\n- Stopped\n- Resumed\n- Destroying\n- Backgrounding (iOS/Mac Catalyst)\n\n\nNow I'll show a practical example demonstrating how to hook into these events for logging purposes.","outputTokens":505,"requestId":"0818:8197A:A7A651:C1765D:69F2A875"},"id":"8f4036ac-758d-434c-8da1-8d0af1c7a813","timestamp":"2026-04-30T00:55:29.957Z","parentId":"5d6a1b61-ecbb-458a-b719-862df49934c2"}
